  "articleSummary": "The article argues that deploying AI in production systems is inherently risky due to unforeseen vulnerabilities like prompt injections, data leaks, and harmful outputs, which most frameworks fail to address proactively. It critiques the gap between demo-stage functionality and real-world safety, emphasizing that large language models (LLMs) lack intrinsic safeguards and will comply with malicious prompts unless explicitly constrained. The solution proposed is **Mastra**, a framework that integrates **input/output processors** as \"middleware\" to enforce guardrails—such as detecting prompt injections, redacting PII,",
